   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Message Eleven Working with the Lord for His Body Scripture Reading: S. S. 6:13 7:13 In Song of Songs 6:13 the lover, having passed through various stages of transformation, has become the Shulammite, Solomon s duplication: She is the same as Solomon in life, nature, expression, and function, as Eve was to Adam Gen 2:20-23.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>This signifies that in the maturity of Christ s life the lover of Christ becomes the same as He is in life, nature, expression, and function but not in the Godhead 2 Cor 3:18; Rom 8:29.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>At this point the Shulammite becomes Solomon s co-worker; this indicates that eventually Christ s lovers need to share in the work of the Lord, working with Him for His Body Eph 4:12; 1 Cor 15:58; 16:10; Col 4:11.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>To share in the Lord s work, we need to be qualified, and our qualification depends on our being equipped with all the attributes of the divine life expressed in human virtues S. S. 7:1-9a: The Spirit reviews the lover s virtues, which are signs of her maturity in the divine life and qualify her to work with the Lord vv.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>1-5; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>2 Cor 1:12; 2:14-17; 11:10a; 1 Thes 2:1-12: The Spirit reviews her beauty in the gospel preaching footsteps in sandals Rom 10:15 and in her standing power thighs produced through the skillful transforming work of God the Spirit jewels 2 Cor 3:18 S. S. 7:1.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Prince s daughter v. 1 indicates that a lover of Christ should reach the maturity in His royal life to reign as a king with Christ Rom 5:17.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Her inward parts navel and belly are filled with the divine life received through the drinking of Christ s blood wine and the eating of His flesh wheat by faith lilies S. S. 7:2; John 6:53-54.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>In Song of Songs 7:3 the Spirit reviews her beauty in her active ability to feed others in a living way John 21:15, 17; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>S. S. 4:5.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>In 7:4 the Spirit reviews her beauty in her submissive will neck wrought by the Spirit s transforming work through sufferings for the carrying out of God s will, in the expression of her heart, which is open to the light, clean, full of rest, and accessible eyes like pools cf.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>1:15; 4:1; 5:12 , and in her spiritual sense of high and sharp discernment nose cf.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Phil 1:9-10; Heb 5:14 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The Spirit reviews her beauty in her thoughts and intentions head , which are strong for God Carmel cf.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>1 Kings 18:19-39 , and in her submission and obedience for her consecration locks of her head cf.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Num 6:5a , which are for the glory of God purple and capture fetter her Beloved, who is the King S. S. 7:5.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>In verses 6 through 9a Christ, the Beloved, offers words of praise for His lover: The Beloved praises her in her beauty and pleasantness, which delight others, and in her mature stature, in which she is like Christ a palm tree Eph 4:13 , and in her rich feeding of others breasts like the clusters S. S. 7:6-7.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The Beloved will enjoy her mature stature of Christ palm tree and share it with the members of His Body branches John 15:5a S. S. 7:8a.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The Beloved wishes that her feeding of others would be rich breasts like clusters of the vine , that her intuition nose would be fragrant for nourishing others in life apples , and that her foretaste would be of the power of the age to come best wine v. 9a; John 2:10; Matt 26:29 S. S. 7:8b-9a.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Song of Songs 7:9b-13 reveals that the lover works with her Beloved for His Body: To share in the work of the Lord is not to work for the Lord but to work with the Lord 1 Cor 3:9a; 2 Cor 6:1a.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>To work with the Lord we need to be one with Him; actually, to work with Christ we must become Christ 1 Cor 6:17; John 15:4-5; Phil 1:21a.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>To work with the Lord we must teach the high truths S. S. 4:8; 1 Tim 2:4.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>To work with the Lord we need the maturity in life Eph 4:13-14: We need to grow and mature unto perfection in the divine life Matt 5:48.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>To enter into God s New Testament economy requires that we grow and mature in the life of God 1 Cor 2:6; Col 1:28.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>To be transformed is to be metabolically changed in our natural life, but to be matured is to be filled with the divine life that changes us Heb 6:1.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Maturity is a matter of having the divine life imparted into us again and again until we have the fullness of life John 10:10b; 2 Cor 5:4b.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>To work with the Lord our work must be for His Body Eph 4:4, 16: The Body is the governing law of the life and work of the children of God today 1:22-23; 1 Cor 12:4-6, 12-13, 27.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The work of the Triune God in us is to produce and build up the Body of Christ Eph 3:16-21; 4:4-6, 12, 16: Our work in the Lord s recovery is the work of God s economy, the work of the Body of Christ 1 Cor 15:58; 16:10; Col 4:11.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>All the co-workers should do the same one work universally for the one unique Body; the starting point of the work is the oneness of the Body Eph 4:4; 1 Cor 16:10.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>According to Song of Songs 7:11, Christ s lover wants to carry out with her Beloved the work that is for the entire world fields by sojourning from one place to another lodging in the villages ; this indicates that our work must be for the Body Eph 4:12.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>In the churches vineyards Christ s lover renders her love to her Beloved S. S. 7:12: At the place of His work, she expresses her love to the Lord: In the midst of the Lord s work, we give Him our love Mark 12:30.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>This kind of fellowship with the Lord is an issue of an absolute union with the Lord in life 1 Cor 6:17; John 14:20; 15:4-5.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>In her working together with her Beloved there is a mutual love signified by mandrakes S. S. 7:13; Gen 30:14-16 giving forth its fragrance between them as a couple who love each other, signifying the bridal love between the lover of Christ and Christ, and in their working places there are plenty of fragrant and choice fruits cf.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Gal 5:22-23; Eph 5:9 , new and old, which she stores up for her Beloved in love.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Here we see the relationship between the first love and the first works Rev 2:4-5: The first works are works that issue from and express the first love.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Only those works that are motivated by the first love are the gold, silver, and precious stones 1 Cor 3:12.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>When we are filled with the first love of the Lord, everything we do issues from and expresses our love for Him Eph 3:19; 4:16.</S>
   </TEXT>
